I thought you might like to have it.

720
00:49:39,562 --> 00:49:40,522
Are you serious?

721
00:49:40,980 --> 00:49:43,525
Well, you love the book that much.
You should have a copy of your own.

722
00:49:44,150 --> 00:49:46,611
-I can't pay you.
-It's a gift.

723
00:49:47,779 --> 00:49:49,114
You've gotten gifts before,
haven't you?

724
00:49:49,280 --> 00:49:50,365
It's been a while.

725
00:49:51,574 --> 00:49:54,911
-Well, it's my way of saying, thanks.
-For what?

726
00:49:56,079 --> 00:49:58,748
That somebody listens...
even if it's just one student.

727
00:49:59,624 --> 00:50:01,001
You're a good teacher, Mr. Carlson.

728
00:50:01,084 --> 00:50:03,294
Listen, we can discuss the book
on Friday in class if you...

729
00:50:03,712 --> 00:50:05,213
...think the Count can
hold their attention.

730
00:50:05,547 --> 00:50:06,715
He's got a shot.

731
00:50:07,549 --> 00:50:08,842
Any particular section
I should read from?

732
00:50:09,592 --> 00:50:12,262
That's easy...the part where
he escapes from prison.

733
00:50:25,942 --> 00:50:28,778
There you go, All Star.
Here's your locker room!

734
00:50:36,327 --> 00:50:40,832
It was only a game...just a touch
football game, nothing more.

735
00:50:41,666 --> 00:50:43,418
But a game I wish we
had never played.

736
00:50:44,461 --> 00:50:48,298
Guards against inmates.
The guards practiced four times a week.

737
00:50:49,132 --> 00:50:51,301
Our team was picked the
Monday before the game.

738
00:50:52,010 --> 00:50:53,511
We had a 2 hour practice.

739
00:50:54,429 --> 00:50:55,638
It didn't matter much.

740
00:50:56,014 --> 00:50:59,017
We weren't supposed to win.
We were just supposed to show up.

741
00:50:59,684 --> 00:51:01,144
Who's the toughest guy here?

742
00:51:02,145 --> 00:51:03,355
How do you mean, tough?

743
00:51:03,855 --> 00:51:05,523
Who can talk and have
everyone listening?

744
00:51:05,690 --> 00:51:07,692
Rizzo. Black kid over there.

745
00:51:09,652 --> 00:51:13,156
Michael saw an opening...a chance
to bring the game to our level.

746
00:51:13,323 --> 00:51:17,327
Even out the field. But he needed help.
He needed Rizzo.

747
00:51:18,161 --> 00:51:22,248
Black kid with an Italian name.
With him on our side, we had a chance.

748
00:51:23,166 --> 00:51:26,169
Look, white boy, I don't know
what you play in the streets.

749
00:51:26,336 --> 00:51:28,588
I don't care. But in here,
the guards call the play...

750
00:51:28,755 --> 00:51:30,382
...and the play calls for
them to win the game.

751
00:51:30,465 --> 00:51:31,216
Why?

752
00:51:31,549 --> 00:51:32,550
Look man...

753
00:51:33,051 --> 00:51:34,552
...guards stay clear of me, all right?

754
00:51:34,719 --> 00:51:36,221
They stay back and let me do my time.

755
00:51:36,554 --> 00:51:38,390
If I play that game and I
put a hurt on one of them...

756
00:51:38,556 --> 00:51:40,183
...they just might change my cushion.

757
00:51:40,392 --> 00:51:43,561
I'm not saying we gotta win.
I just don't want to take a beating.

758
00:51:44,104 --> 00:51:45,063
You do every day.

759
00:51:45,772 --> 00:51:49,067
-Why is Saturday special?
-'Cause on Saturday, we can hit back.

760
00:51:52,237 --> 00:51:55,281
They don't fuck with you like they do us,
but they fuck with you another way!

761
00:51:55,448 --> 00:51:56,700
You're just an animal to them.

762
00:51:57,867 --> 00:52:00,537
-I don't give a fuck!
-Yeah, you do.

763
00:52:00,912 --> 00:52:03,415
And beating them on Saturday
is not gonna change a thing.

764
00:52:04,290 --> 00:52:05,458
Then why, white boy, why?

765
00:52:05,625 --> 00:52:10,005
To make them feel what we feel
...just for a couple of hours.

766
00:52:12,215 --> 00:52:14,009
Now, don't try anything funny, Sambo.

767
00:52:14,217 --> 00:52:16,344
Nobody will get hurt.
You know what I'm saying?

768
00:52:16,761 --> 00:52:17,679
I call heads.

769
00:52:20,807 --> 00:52:22,809
He called heads.
It is a head.

770
00:52:24,769 --> 00:52:25,687
Let's go.

771
00:52:35,947 --> 00:52:39,284
You're gonna die, mother fucker!
You're gonna fucking die!

772
00:52:50,003 --> 00:52:52,005
None of you motherfuckers can cover me!

773
00:52:52,339 --> 00:52:55,675
We got ourselves a game!
I'm feeling good today.

774
00:52:56,176 --> 00:52:57,344
This shit feels good.

775
00:53:04,392 --> 00:53:05,352
Fuck!

776
00:53:11,775 --> 00:53:13,777
Get the fuck off me!

777
00:53:25,080 --> 00:53:27,874
Yeah, keep smiling, you little piss ant.

778
00:53:30,877 --> 00:53:33,546
For 90 minutes, we took
the game out of the prison...

779
00:53:34,172 --> 00:53:36,091
...moved it miles beyond
the locked gates...

780
00:53:36,257 --> 00:53:38,385
...and the sloping hills of
the surrounding countryside...

781
00:53:39,010 --> 00:53:41,805
...and brought it back down to the streets
of the neighborhoods we'd come from.

782
00:53:43,056 --> 00:53:45,892
For those 90 minutes,
we were once again free!

783
00:54:04,744 --> 00:54:06,246
Rizzo! Rizzo!

784
00:54:18,174 --> 00:54:21,970
Rizzo...Rizzo.

785
00:54:23,680 --> 00:54:26,850
Hey, Nokes.
Good game.

786
00:54:29,769 --> 00:54:33,106
For once, we had a victory.
But it didn't last.

787
00:54:33,773 --> 00:54:38,111
It couldn't last...
and all I wanted to do was die.

788
00:54:39,195 --> 00:54:43,199
I was not alone in the hole. I knew my
friends were down in the depths with me.

789
00:54:43,742 --> 00:54:48,038
Each in his own cell, each in his own
pain...suffering his own demons.

790
00:54:48,663 --> 00:54:49,789
Rizzo was there, too.

791
00:54:52,834 --> 00:54:54,502
I had lost any sense of time.

792
00:55:35,377 --> 00:55:36,544
I thought you'd never wake up.

793
00:55:37,879 --> 00:55:39,214
I thought I'd never want to.

794
00:55:39,589 --> 00:55:42,759
John and Tommy, they're
on the other side there.

795
00:55:44,302 --> 00:55:47,972
How are they?
They're alive.

796
00:55:49,766 --> 00:55:50,767
Who isn't?

797
00:55:52,727 --> 00:55:53,687
Rizzo.

798
00:55:56,398 --> 00:55:57,565
They killed him?

799
00:55:59,567 --> 00:56:03,780
They took turns beating him until
there was nothing of that kid to beat.

800
00:56:08,702 --> 00:56:10,120
Rizzo was dead because of us.

801
00:56:11,538 --> 00:56:13,540
We made him think that going
up against the guards...

802
00:56:13,623 --> 00:56:15,041
...in a meaningless football game...

803
00:56:15,208 --> 00:56:18,795
...had some value...that it would
give us a reason to go on.

804
00:56:19,963 --> 00:56:21,673
Once again, we were wrong.

805
00:56:24,843 --> 00:56:26,177
Did they give you
your release date yet?

806
00:56:26,344 --> 00:56:27,679
Nokes had a letter from the warden.

807
00:56:28,513 --> 00:56:30,390
Waved it in front of me,
then tore it up....

808
00:56:31,558 --> 00:56:32,392
When do you figure?

809
00:56:34,185 --> 00:56:36,396
End of spring, early
summer or something.

810
00:56:37,480 --> 00:56:39,024
I wish we were coming with you.

811
00:56:40,066 --> 00:56:42,402
It would've been nice for all
of us to walk out together.

812
00:56:43,403 --> 00:56:46,740
No use thinking about that. We're
gonna do a full year, not an hour less.

813
00:56:48,783 --> 00:56:52,120
When I get out, I could get Father
Bobby to make a couple of phone calls.

814
00:56:52,328 --> 00:56:53,747
Shave a month or two off.

815
00:56:53,913 --> 00:56:56,583
-There's nothing to talk about!
-There's a lot to talk about.

816
00:56:57,083 --> 00:57:00,003
Maybe, if people knew what was going
on in here, they'd make a move.

817
00:57:00,587 --> 00:57:02,255
I don't want anybody to know.

818
00:57:03,048 --> 00:57:06,760
Not Father Bobby, King Benny,
Fat Mancho...

819
00:57:06,926 --> 00:57:09,262
...not my mother. Nobody.

820
00:57:10,889 --> 00:57:12,432
I don't either.

821
00:57:12,515 --> 00:57:14,768
I mean, I wouldn't know what
to say to anyone who did know.

822
00:57:15,477 --> 00:57:18,146
I can't think of anybody
who needs to hear about it.

823
00:57:19,314 --> 00:57:21,858
Either they won't believe it,
or they won't give a shit.

824
00:57:22,817 --> 00:57:25,111
Yeah, I don't even think we should
talk about it once it's over.

825
00:57:27,447 --> 00:57:31,451
We got no choice but to live with it.
And talking makes living it harder.

826
00:57:32,827 --> 00:57:34,996
So, we might as well
not even talk about it.

827
00:57:35,997 --> 00:57:37,332
The truth stays with us.

828
00:57:40,502 --> 00:57:42,337
I want to be able to sleep one night...

829
00:57:43,880 --> 00:57:47,467
...and not have to worry who's coming
in my room, what's gonna happen to me.

830
00:57:51,221 --> 00:57:55,183
If I can get that, then I'll be happy.

831
00:57:57,852 --> 00:58:00,647
Someday, John, I promise.

832
00:58:17,330 --> 00:58:20,834
I was in my last hours as an inmate
at the Wilkinson Home for boys.

833
00:58:21,668 --> 00:58:23,586
I was given four copies
of my release form.

834
00:58:23,962 --> 00:58:26,256
The final reminder of my
time at Wilkinson.

835
00:58:28,717 --> 00:58:30,301
I never heard the key
turn in the lock...

836
00:58:30,885 --> 00:58:32,971
...and I never heard
the snap of the bolt.

837
00:58:34,472 --> 00:58:35,807
You should be asleep.

838
00:58:37,058 --> 00:58:41,104
I just wanted to say goodbye.
We all do.

839
00:58:44,107 --> 00:58:46,109
I told him. I told him right
to his face. I said,

840
00:58:46,276 --> 00:58:48,111
I don't care if you're paying me
overtime or not.

841
00:58:48,194 --> 00:58:49,738
I'm not working those kind of hours.

842
00:58:49,946 --> 00:58:51,281
Yeah, did you put in for it?

843
00:58:51,781 --> 00:58:52,741
I put in for it!

844
00:58:52,782 --> 00:58:54,492
Because I put in for it.
They don't give it to me.

845
00:58:55,118 --> 00:58:58,329
I come in early for three days.
Do they give me overtime? No!

846
00:58:59,497 --> 00:59:01,458
A part of all of us was
left there that night.

847
00:59:02,500 --> 00:59:04,836
That night will never be
removed from my mind.

848
00:59:05,420 --> 00:59:09,966
The night of June 1, 1968--
the Summer of Love.

849
00:59:11,634 --> 00:59:13,636
My last night at the
Wilkinson Home for boys.

850
01:00:00,308 --> 01:00:02,977
At 8:25 p.m. two men
walked through the doors.

851
01:00:03,978 --> 01:00:07,065
The bartender knew their faces as most
of the neighborhood knew their names.

852
01:00:07,482 --> 01:00:10,110
They were two of the founding
members of the West Side Boys.

853
01:00:10,193 --> 01:00:11,695
They were also its deadliest.

854
01:00:13,780 --> 01:00:16,783
The blond-haired man had been in and out
of jail since he was a teenager.

855
01:00:17,367 --> 01:00:19,452
He robbed and killed
at will or on command.

856
01:00:20,286 --> 01:00:22,956
He was presently a suspect in
four unsolved homicides.

857
01:00:23,540 --> 01:00:27,127
He was an alcoholic and a cocaine abuser
with a fast temper and a faster trigger.

858
01:00:27,585 --> 01:00:30,422
He once shot a mechanic dead for
moving ahead of him in a movie line.

859
01:00:32,716 --> 01:00:34,718
The dark-haired man was equally deadly...

860
01:00:34,759 --> 01:00:37,053
...and had committed his
first murder at the age of 17.

861
01:00:37,929 --> 01:00:41,766
In return, he was paid $50.
He drank, and he did drugs...

862
01:00:41,933 --> 01:00:45,061
...and he had a wife he never saw,
living somewhere in Queens.

863
01:00:47,772 --> 01:00:51,192
He's making a noble attempt
to really change things.

864
01:00:51,276 --> 01:00:54,946
-The Republicans will take the House.
-Well, we got a lot of work to do.

865
01:00:55,071 --> 01:00:56,740
It's gonna take more
than 4 years to get....

866
01:00:56,906 --> 01:00:58,116
They'll take it at
the mid-term elections.

867
01:00:58,616 --> 01:01:01,453
He's got the charisma.
He's gonna do it.

868
01:01:01,661 --> 01:01:04,330
He's our man. Reagan's
the man who's gonna do it.

869
01:01:05,957 --> 01:01:08,168
Hey, Jerry...
What are they talking about?

870
01:01:08,585 --> 01:01:10,587
They're talking about Reagan's speech.

871
01:01:13,590 --> 01:01:16,092
Order those two men some
drinks and put it on my tab.

872
01:01:18,011 --> 01:01:20,847
You tell them that Republicans
are not welcome in Hell's Kitchen...

873
01:01:21,014 --> 01:01:24,517
...and either a political conversion or
a change of conversation is in order.

874
01:01:24,934 --> 01:01:25,935
Sure thing.

875
01:01:32,984 --> 01:01:35,904
The gentlemen there would like to
buy you a drink on one condition.

876
01:01:36,196 --> 01:01:39,908
You know the rules:
no religion, no politics.

877
01:01:40,533 --> 01:01:41,659
You get my meaning?

878
01:01:59,552 --> 01:02:01,846
Order something for me.
I gotta go to the bathroom.

879
01:02:32,711 --> 01:02:33,837
Can I help you with something, chief?

880
01:02:35,714 --> 01:02:40,093
Not right now.
Enjoy the rest of your meal.

881
01:03:25,930 --> 01:03:30,143
I ordered brisket on a roll,
with fries and...

882
01:03:31,561 --> 01:03:34,314
...two baskets of soda bread.
I know how you like that shit.

883
01:03:35,440 --> 01:03:36,441
Is that okay by you?

884
01:03:38,818 --> 01:03:41,905
Take a look at the guy at the table.
Take a good look.

885
01:03:53,750 --> 01:03:54,834
Motherfucker.

886
01:04:21,361 --> 01:04:22,946
That's him.

887
01:04:23,238 --> 01:04:24,656
Are you fucking kidding me?

888
01:04:28,201 --> 01:04:28,910
Bingo!

889
01:04:54,644 --> 01:04:55,770
This is amazing.

890
01:04:55,937 --> 01:04:58,606
Hello...it's been a long time!

891
01:05:00,358 --> 01:05:01,443
Who the fuck are you guys?

892
01:05:05,822 --> 01:05:07,407
Who the fuck asked you to sit down?

893
01:05:07,907 --> 01:05:10,994
I thought you'd be happy to see us.
I guess I was wrong.

894
01:05:12,829 --> 01:05:15,248
You know, I thought
you'd do a lot better.

895
01:05:15,915 --> 01:05:18,126
You know, with all that training...
all that time you put in...

896
01:05:18,752 --> 01:05:20,795
...just to end up watching
someone else's money.

897
01:05:21,129 --> 01:05:22,422
That seems like a waste.

898
01:05:22,630 --> 01:05:24,591
I'm asking you now for the last
time, what the fuck do you want?

899
01:05:24,799 --> 01:05:26,509
Why don't you take your time?
It'll come to you.

900
01:05:32,307 --> 01:05:34,100
I can see how he might forget us.

901
01:05:34,768 --> 01:05:37,687
You know, we were just something for
you and your friends to play with.

902
01:05:37,854 --> 01:05:39,981
It's a little harder for us to forget.

903
01:05:40,357 --> 01:05:42,609
You gave us so much more to remember.

904
01:05:45,987 --> 01:05:47,364
You can't quite place us,
can you, chief?

905
01:05:48,114 --> 01:05:52,118
Let me help you out. You're looking
at John Reilly and Tommy Marcano.

906
01:06:03,588 --> 01:06:04,506
Yeah, that's right.

907
01:06:11,304 --> 01:06:12,639
That was a long time ago.

908
01:06:16,184 --> 01:06:16,935
So how you been?

909
01:06:17,936 --> 01:06:19,437
Yeah, we ain't kids now.

910
01:06:20,730 --> 01:06:22,065
So, what do you want?

911
01:06:22,899 --> 01:06:26,236
What I've always wanted
is to watch you die!

912
01:06:32,283 --> 01:06:33,326
You ordered the meat loaf.

913
01:06:34,953 --> 01:06:37,956
The brisket's really good here,
only you'll never know it.

914
01:06:39,249 --> 01:06:40,083
You fucked up.

915
01:06:53,888 --> 01:06:58,226
Yeah, you were scared little pricks,
both of you.

916
01:06:59,769 --> 01:07:04,441
All of you...scared shitless.
But l...

917
01:07:06,359 --> 01:07:09,821
...l tried to make you tough.
I tried to make you hard.

918
01:07:09,863 --> 01:07:13,491
I had you all wrong then, Nokes.
All this time I thought you just liked...

919
01:07:13,658 --> 01:07:15,160
...fucking and beating up little boys.

920
01:07:15,368 --> 01:07:17,620
You two motherfuckers
are gonna burn in hell!

921
01:07:18,204 --> 01:07:19,539
You're gonna burn in hell.

922
01:07:19,706 --> 01:07:20,665
Yeah, after you.

923
01:07:26,463 --> 01:07:27,630
Did that hurt, Nokes?

924
01:08:05,168 --> 01:08:09,422
Jerry, sorry, should've made
those brisket sandwiches to go.

925
01:08:22,018 --> 01:08:23,353
John Reilly, how do you plead?

926
01:08:23,728 --> 01:08:24,896
Not guilty, Your Honor.

927
01:08:25,855 --> 01:08:26,731
Thomas Marcano?

928
01:08:28,233 --> 01:08:29,401
Not guilty, Your Honor.

929
01:08:29,943 --> 01:08:33,655
John Reilly and Thomas Marcano,
you are hereby held without bail.

930
01:08:34,864 --> 01:08:38,284
In all the years since Wilkinson's, we
had never once spoken to each other...

931
01:08:38,451 --> 01:08:41,788
...about what happened there.
We remained caring friends...

932
01:08:41,955 --> 01:08:43,957
...but the relationship
had been altered.

933
01:08:45,125 --> 01:08:49,295
We drifted together, always wondering
if that moment would arrive...

934
01:08:49,754 --> 01:08:51,506
...that would force us to
deal with the past.

935
01:09:05,020 --> 01:09:08,356
One down, Shakes, one down.

936
01:09:10,358 --> 01:09:11,192
One what?

937
01:09:13,445 --> 01:09:16,781
One Sean Nokes.

938
01:09:17,949 --> 01:09:18,825
Nokes?

939
01:09:27,125 --> 01:09:28,376
At the time of Nokes' shooting,

940
01:09:28,418 --> 01:09:31,379
Michael was working as an
Assistant New York District Attorney.

941
01:09:31,838 --> 01:09:34,591
I got a call that he wanted to meet me
on 45th Street in Queens.

942
01:09:35,425 --> 01:09:36,384
Then, he hung up.

943
01:09:40,930 --> 01:09:42,640
-So, what did they say?
-What?

944
01:09:42,891 --> 01:09:44,142
John and Tommy, what'd they say?

945
01:09:44,309 --> 01:09:45,643
It's a little cloak and
dagger, isn't it, Mike?

946
01:09:46,561 --> 01:09:48,563
Nokes?
Did they talk about him?

947
01:09:50,482 --> 01:09:51,816
-John did.
-Yeah?

948
01:09:52,692 --> 01:09:53,693
What did he say?

949
01:09:54,527 --> 01:09:57,155
He said, "One down, Shakes.
One down."

950
01:10:00,700 --> 01:10:02,702
I hear they hired Danny Snyder
as the lawyer, is that right?

951
01:10:02,869 --> 01:10:05,372
It's temporary. King Benny's
gonna move in one of his lawyers.

952
01:10:05,622 --> 01:10:08,291
Don't let him do that.
Snyder's perfect.

953
01:10:08,541 --> 01:10:10,919
-Perfect? The guy's a fall down drunk!
-Then he is perfect.

954
01:10:11,419 --> 01:10:12,545
Perfect for what?

955
