02:15:25,911 --> 02:15:28,288
There's always gonna be more
bad guys than good, Mikey.

1887
02:15:30,249 --> 02:15:32,918
And can you imagine the work you'd
get from John and Tommy's crew?

1888
02:15:34,002 --> 02:15:35,295
That's a house and a pool.

1889
02:15:37,840 --> 02:15:42,010
Not for me. I've seen
all the law I want to see.

1890
02:15:43,470 --> 02:15:46,140
-It's time for something else.
-Like what?

1891
02:15:46,640 --> 02:15:47,975
I'll let you know when I know.

1892
02:15:49,184 --> 02:15:51,729
You know, you're too old to
play for the Yankees...

1893
02:15:51,812 --> 02:15:53,188
...and you're too young to take up golf.

1894
02:15:53,647 --> 02:15:55,482
Why are you shooting holes
through all of my plans?

1895
02:15:55,649 --> 02:15:56,692
You gonna make me panic.

1896
02:15:58,444 --> 02:15:59,778
You'll work it out.
You always have.

1897
02:16:05,993 --> 02:16:07,578
It's time for quiet, Shakes.

1898
02:16:09,705 --> 02:16:12,916
I just want to shut my eyes and not
have to see the places I've been.

1899
02:16:15,836 --> 02:16:16,879
I'm weary...

1900
02:16:21,425 --> 02:16:22,468
I don't know.

1901
02:16:25,554 --> 02:16:27,765
Maybe I'll get lucky,
forget I was even there.

1902
02:16:29,391 --> 02:16:31,351
Well, don't disappear on me,
counselor.

1903
02:16:32,936 --> 02:16:34,730
I may need a good lawyer one day.

1904
02:16:34,938 --> 02:16:36,065
You can't afford a good lawyer.

1905
02:16:39,068 --> 02:16:40,569
I may need a good friend, though.

1906
02:16:43,947 --> 02:16:46,283
I'll find you when you do.
Count on it.

1907
02:16:48,452 --> 02:16:49,578
Always have.

1908
02:16:56,251 --> 02:16:59,797
A full month had passed since the
acquittal, and no one had made contact.

1909
02:17:00,381 --> 02:17:03,050
In those few weeks, our lives had
reverted back to what they'd been...

1910
02:17:03,217 --> 02:17:05,052
...prior to the murder of Sean Nokes.

1911
02:17:05,677 --> 02:17:09,014
Carol had returned to her
stack of social service files...

1912
02:17:09,223 --> 02:17:10,641
...helping troubled teens
and single mothers.

1913
02:17:11,475 --> 02:17:15,145
John and Tommy went back to the
streets, running the West Side Boys.

1914
02:17:15,938 --> 02:17:20,067
I was promoted from clerk to reporter
trainee, covering the entertainment beat.

1915
02:17:20,818 --> 02:17:23,070
Michael, as he'd promised,
resigned from his job...

1916
02:17:23,278 --> 02:17:25,489
...after working the losing
end of a "can't miss case".

1917
02:17:30,744 --> 02:17:32,496
I don't know how to fucking thank you!

1918
02:17:36,959 --> 02:17:39,628
I can't believe what you did.
I can't believe we got away with it!

1919
02:17:39,795 --> 02:17:42,673
It wasn't me. That was Mikey.
It was all Mikey's plan.

1920
02:17:42,840 --> 02:17:45,467
When I first heard he was taking the
case, I was gonna have him burned.

1921
02:17:46,510 --> 02:17:49,179
I figured, he's a friend, and if you've
gotta be sent away on a murder rap...

1922
02:17:49,346 --> 02:17:50,013
...who better to do it?

1923
02:17:50,180 --> 02:17:52,850
Well, the way he was handling the case,
I thought he sucked as a lawyer.

1924
02:17:53,058 --> 02:17:54,476
I started feeling sorry for the bastard.

1925
02:17:55,477 --> 02:17:56,937
Never feel sorry for a lawyer.

1926
02:17:58,021 --> 02:17:59,481
Get over here, counselor!

1927
02:18:00,441 --> 02:18:02,693
You are the real Count!

1928
02:18:02,860 --> 02:18:05,154
Alive and well and
living in New York City!

1929
02:18:07,322 --> 02:18:09,658
You fucking maniac! All right!

1930
02:18:11,869 --> 02:18:13,370
What is this, a gay bar?

1931
02:18:15,039 --> 02:18:16,373
It was until you came in!

1932
02:18:16,665 --> 02:18:18,208
Why don't you give me a
kiss to go with that hello?

1933
02:18:24,882 --> 02:18:26,717
Get out of the way.

1934
02:18:32,389 --> 02:18:33,307
Let's have a drink.

1935
02:18:39,188 --> 02:18:40,522
The Four Gladiators!

1936
02:18:41,940 --> 02:18:45,694
The "Four Gladiators", worst quartet
to ever hold a Hell's Kitchen corner.

1937
02:18:46,695 --> 02:18:48,697
But what was that name that
Shakes wanted to call it?

1938
02:18:48,947 --> 02:18:52,159
Genius wanted to call it,
"The Count and His Cristos."

1939
02:18:52,409 --> 02:18:54,661
-Nice!
-Well, you know, it's so sweet, isn't it?

1940
02:18:56,288 --> 02:18:58,290
Hey, that would've sent albums
flying out of the store.

1941
02:18:58,457 --> 02:19:00,876
We weren't that bad. I mean,
some people wanted to hear us sing.

1942
02:19:01,043 --> 02:19:02,753
That kid at the deaf school don't count!

1943
02:19:07,800 --> 02:19:08,926
One song for Carol.

1944
02:19:09,635 --> 02:19:11,887
-I retired a long time ago.
-Come on, you mutts!

1945
02:19:12,262 --> 02:19:14,264
Don't you guys have to go out
and shoot somebody?

1946
02:19:19,937 --> 02:19:22,064
We always got time for a song!

1947
02:19:23,524 --> 02:19:25,275
Just kidding, you know what I'm saying?

1948
02:19:26,902 --> 02:19:28,487
You pick it, Mikey.
Nothing too slow.

1949
02:19:28,862 --> 02:19:29,696
Start us up.

1950
02:19:33,450 --> 02:19:35,786
-How many songs do you know?
-One.

1951
02:19:41,625 --> 02:19:46,296
"Walk...like...a...man!"

1952
02:19:49,299 --> 02:19:51,301
"Walk like a man..."

1953
02:19:51,468 --> 02:19:52,678
"...fast as you can..."

1954
02:19:53,178 --> 02:19:56,515
"Walk...like a man, my son..."

1955
02:19:57,641 --> 02:20:00,894
"Go tell the world...
forget about the girl!"

1956
02:20:01,186 --> 02:20:02,896
Don't forget about the girl!

1957
02:20:17,161 --> 02:20:19,496
On March 16, 1984...

1958
02:20:19,663 --> 02:20:22,791
John Reilly's bloated body was found
face up in a tenement building...

1959
02:20:23,292 --> 02:20:25,586
...right next to the bottle of
boiler gin that killed him.

1960
02:20:26,170 --> 02:20:29,882
At the time of his death, he was a
suspect in five unsolved homicides.

1961
02:20:30,257 --> 02:20:32,676
He was two weeks past
his 29th birthday.

1962
02:20:37,723 --> 02:20:41,185
Thomas Marcano died on July 26, 1985.

1963
02:20:41,351 --> 02:20:43,812
He was shot at close range 5 times.

1964
02:20:44,188 --> 02:20:46,607
The body lay undiscovered
for more than a week.

1965
02:20:47,066 --> 02:20:50,235
There was a crucifix and a picture
of Saint Jude in his pocket.

1966
02:20:50,611 --> 02:20:52,071
He was 29 years old.

1967
02:20:54,448 --> 02:20:57,534
Michael Sullivan lives in a small
town in the English countryside...

1968
02:20:57,701 --> 02:20:59,370
...where he works part-time
as a carpenter.

1969
02:21:00,079 --> 02:21:02,915
He no longer practices law,
and he has never married.

1970
02:21:03,582 --> 02:21:05,292
He lives quietly and alone.

1971
02:21:08,087 --> 02:21:12,257
Carol still works for a Social Service
agency and lives in Hell's Kitchen.

1972
02:21:12,800 --> 02:21:13,926
She has never married...

1973
02:21:14,301 --> 02:21:16,929
...but is a single mother supporting
a growing 12-year-old son.

1974
02:21:18,138 --> 02:21:22,476
The boy, John Thomas Michael
Martinez, loves to read...

1975
02:21:22,935 --> 02:21:24,520
...and is called Shakes by his mother.

1976
02:21:27,481 --> 02:21:30,984
It was our special night, and we
held it for as long as we could.

1977
02:21:31,527 --> 02:21:32,903
It was our happy ending.

1978
02:21:33,904 --> 02:21:36,323
And the last time we would
ever be together again.

1979
02:22:25,914 --> 02:22:28,042
The future lay sparkling ahead...

1980
02:22:28,417 --> 02:22:30,586
...and we thought we would
know each other forever.

